# verification

@verify_container_down `HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_DARWIN_MARKER=1 HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_CWD_SHORTCIRCUIT=1 HEXA_RESOLVER_FORCE_DOWN=1 HEXA_DOCKER_BIN=/usr/bin/false hexa --version` → exit 76 with trailer:
  ```
  hexa-resolver[hard]: docker daemon down — refusing bare-Mac fallback (rc=76)
  reason: container-down: Docker Desktop daemon not responding to 'docker info'
  fix: 1) open -a Docker  2) docker context use desktop-linux  3) HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_REROUTE=1 hexa <cmd>   # escape hatch: bare-Mac exec, dangerous (no cgroup caps)
  ```

@verify_image_missing `HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_DARWIN_MARKER=1 HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_CWD_SHORTCIRCUIT=1 HEXA_RESOLVER_FORCE_DOWN=1 HEXA_DOCKER_IMAGE=nonexistent:foo hexa --version` → exit 76 with trailer:
  ```
  hexa-resolver[hard]: image nonexistent:foo not present — refusing bare-Mac fallback (rc=76)
  reason: image-missing: docker image 'nonexistent:foo' absent (build pipeline gap or pruned)
  fix: 1) docker pull nonexistent:foo  2) (cd $HEXA_LANG && bash scripts/build-hexa-runner-image.sh)   # rebuild from hexa-lang  3) HEXA_DOCKER_IMAGE=<alt-tag> hexa <cmd>   # use alternate image tag
  ```

@verify_ssh_fail in-process bash unit test of the case statement + trailer emission for reason="타임아웃 (네트워크/방화벽)" cand=hetzner → emits `reason: ssh-fail: 타임아웃 (네트워크/방화벽)` + 3 fix candidates.

@verify_rsync_eperm in-process bash unit test of the case statement + trailer emission for rsync_rc=23 rsync_last="rsync: rename failed: Operation not permitted (1)" HOST=ubu1 → emits `reason: rsync-eperm: rsync rc=23 on host=ubu1 (...)` + 3 fix candidates.

@verify_syntax bash -n on both ~/.hx/bin/hexa and scripts/bin/hexa_remote → PASS

